cdx6500PCTFRDTEPortTable.name: cdx6500PCTFRDTEPortTable
cdx6500PCTFRDTEPortTable.description: All of the configuration parameters relevant to the Frame Relay DTE Port table.

cdx6500PCTFRDTEPortEntry.name: cdx6500PCTFRDTEPortEntry
cdx6500PCTFRDTEPortEntry.description: A row of FRI Port configuration parameters.

cdx6500frdtepCfgPortNum.name: cdx6500frdtepCfgPortNum
cdx6500frdtepCfgPortNum.description: Specifies the Port number for the Frame Relay Interface port you are selecting.

cdx6500frdtepConnectionType.name: cdx6500frdtepConnectionType
cdx6500frdtepConnectionType.description: Specify the control signal handshake and clocking required for a connection to be made to this port: simp - simple, no control signals required dtr - dedicated, require the data terminal ready signal (DTR) simpb - simple, no control signals required for data transmission and reception. By default output leads will be low. nc - Skipped during configuration.

cdx6500frdtepClockSource.name: cdx6500frdtepClockSource
cdx6500frdtepClockSource.description: int - internal clock source ext - external clock source extint - Internal receive and external transmit clock source (DCE only). extlp - external receive and loopback transmit clock source (DTE only). EXTLP must be configured in conjunction with EXTINT. nc - Skipped during configuration.

cdx6500frdtepClockSpeed.name: cdx6500frdtepClockSpeed
cdx6500frdtepClockSpeed.description: This is the speed of the port in bits per second, when using internal clocking. The highest available speed is dependent on the card type,and on the interface type.

cdx6500frdtepMaxStations.name: cdx6500frdtepMaxStations
cdx6500frdtepMaxStations.description: This is the highest station number to be configured on this FRI port. It is used to limit the configuration of stations.

cdx6500frdtepFrameSeqCounting.name: cdx6500frdtepFrameSeqCounting
cdx6500frdtepFrameSeqCounting.description: Port uses normal or extended frame sequence numbering: normal - normal sequencing (modulo 8) ext - extended sequencing (modulo 128) nc - Skipped during configuration. All stations on this port will be set to this value.

cdx6500frdtepPktSeqCounting.name: cdx6500frdtepPktSeqCounting
cdx6500frdtepPktSeqCounting.description: Port uses normal or extended packet level sequence numbers normal - normal sequencing (Modulo 8) ext - extended sequencing (Modulo 128) nc - Skipped during configuration. This parameter must be set to the same value at both this FRI port and the remote FRI port. All stations on this port will be set to this value.

cdx6500frdtepCtrlProtocol.name: cdx6500frdtepCtrlProtocol
cdx6500frdtepCtrlProtocol.description: Whether ANSI T1.617 Annex D or LMI Support is enabled none - None is enabled. annexD - Annex D is enabled lmi - LMI is enabled. annexA - Annex A is enabled. auto - Auto-learn the Network control protocol type nc - Skipped during configuration.

cdx6500frdtepT391.name: cdx6500frdtepT391
cdx6500frdtepT391.description: This parameter is the Link Integrity Verification Timer polling period. The FRI port sends status enquiry messages to network every T391/nT1 seconds.

cdx6500frdtepT392.name: cdx6500frdtepT392
cdx6500frdtepT392.description: This parameter is the polling Cycle Verification Timer period. The FRI port expects status enquiry messages every T392/nT2 seconds. This parameter must be set to a value greater than N391/nT1, and applies only in bi-directional mode.

cdx6500frdtepN391.name: cdx6500frdtepN391
cdx6500frdtepN391.description: Full Status polling cycle. FRI port sends Full status enquiry messages to network every nN1 polls.

cdx6500frdtepN392.name: cdx6500frdtepN392
cdx6500frdtepN392.description: Error inactivity threshold. Number of errors during NN3 events that cause the station to be declared inactive. Should be less than or equal to nN3.

cdx6500frdtepN393.name: cdx6500frdtepN393
cdx6500frdtepN393.description: Monitored events count for measuring nN3. nN2 errors during nN3 events will cause the station to be declared inactive. Should be greater than nN3.

cdx6500frdtepNT1.name: cdx6500frdtepNT1
cdx6500frdtepNT1.description: This parameter is the Link Integrity Verification Timer polling period. The FRI port sends status enquiry messages to network every T391/nT1 seconds.

cdx6500frdtepNT2.name: cdx6500frdtepNT2
cdx6500frdtepNT2.description: This parameter is the polling Cycle Verification Timer period. The FRI port expects status enquiry messages every T392/nT2 seconds. This parameter must be set to a value greater than N391/nT1, and applies only in bi-directional mode.

cdx6500frdtepNN1.name: cdx6500frdtepNN1
cdx6500frdtepNN1.description: Full Status polling cycle. FRI port sends Full status enquiry messages to network every nN1 polls.

cdx6500frdtepNN2.name: cdx6500frdtepNN2
cdx6500frdtepNN2.description: Error inactivity threshold. Number of errors during NN3 events that cause the station to be declared inactive. Should be less than or equal to nN3.

cdx6500frdtepNN3.name: cdx6500frdtepNN3
cdx6500frdtepNN3.description: Monitored events count for measuring nN3. nN2 errors during nN3 events will cause the station to be declared inactive. Should be greater than nN3.

cdx6500frdtepHighPriorityStn.name: cdx6500frdtepHighPriorityStn
cdx6500frdtepHighPriorityStn.description: This parameter specifies a station who's PVC status has priority over all other stations when FRI same port back up is enabled. When the network reports this DLCI inactive, an alternate connection over a backup link is attempted.

cdx6500frdtepMaxVoiceBWBitsPerSec.name: cdx6500frdtepMaxVoiceBWBitsPerSec
cdx6500frdtepMaxVoiceBWBitsPerSec.description: This parameter limits the bandwidth, in bits per sec (including overhead), for voice traffic passing through this frame relay port. A zero value disables any voice passing through this port.

cdx6500frdtepSegSizeVoicePresent.name: cdx6500frdtepSegSizeVoicePresent
cdx6500frdtepSegSizeVoicePresent.description: Data packets to be segmented into this maximum frame size when voice is active on this port. segSize32 - 32 byte segments segSize64 - 64 byte segments segSize128 - 128 byte segments segSize256 - 256 byte segments segSize512 - 512 byte segments segSize1024 - 1024 byte segments nc - Skipped during configuration.

cdx6500frdtepSegSizeVoiceNotPresent.name: cdx6500frdtepSegSizeVoiceNotPresent
cdx6500frdtepSegSizeVoiceNotPresent.description: Data packets to be segmented into this maximum frame size when voice is not active on this port. segSize32 - 32 byte segments segSize64 - 64 byte segments segSize128 - 128 byte segments segSize256 - 256 byte segments segSize512 - 512 byte segments segSize1024 - 1024 byte segments segSize2048 - 2048 byte segments segSize4096 - 4096 byte segments disable - segment size is 32768 bytes nc - Skipped during configuration.

cdx6500frdtepInvertTXClock.name: cdx6500frdtepInvertTXClock
cdx6500frdtepInvertTXClock.description: This parameter specifies whether the phase of the transmit clock should be inverted. Note: This parameter is primarily for X.21 electrical interfaces. no - Don't invert. yes - Invert.

cdx6500frdtepControlProtocolOptions.name: cdx6500frdtepControlProtocolOptions
cdx6500frdtepControlProtocolOptions.description: These options control the PVC management protocol none - No option selected async - The port will send/receive asynchronous A-bit if it is performing Network side protocol functionality nbit - The port will send and accept N-bit messages dbit - The port will send and accept D-bit messages This forces ASYNC to be specified (dbit+async)

cdx6500frdtepDiscardControlOptions.name: cdx6500frdtepDiscardControlOptions
cdx6500frdtepDiscardControlOptions.description: This parameter controls the discard frame options none - No option selected debit - DE marked frames are discarded before non-DE frames

cdx6500frdtepElectricalInterfaceType.name: cdx6500frdtepElectricalInterfaceType
cdx6500frdtepElectricalInterfaceType.description: Specify the Electrical Interface Type: V.24 - V.24 Electrical Interface Type V.35 - V.35 Electrical Interface Type V.36 - V.36 Electrical Interface Type X.21 - X.21 Electrical Interface Type NONE - Electrically disabled

cdx6500frdtepV24ElectricalInterfaceOptio.name: cdx6500frdtepV24ElectricalInterfaceOption
cdx6500frdtepV24ElectricalInterfaceOptio.description: Specify the Pin 22 option: RI - V.24 uses Pin 22 for Ring Indicator output signal TM - V.24 uses Pin 22 for Test Mode input signal

cdx6500frdtepHighSpeedElectricalInterfac.name: cdx6500frdtepHighSpeedElectricalInterfaceOption
cdx6500frdtepHighSpeedElectricalInterfac.description: Specify the cable type: NONE - V.35/V.36/X.21 DCE with straight through cable XOVER - V.35/V.36/X.21 DCE with crossover adapter cable

cdx6500PPSTFRDTEPortTable.name: cdx6500PPSTFRDTEPortTable
cdx6500PPSTFRDTEPortTable.description: All of the statistics parameters relevant to the Frame Relay DTE Port table.

cdx6500PPSTFRDTEPortEntry.name: cdx6500PPSTFRDTEPortEntry
cdx6500PPSTFRDTEPortEntry.description: A row of Frame Relay DTE Port statistics parameters.

cdx6500frdtepStatsPortNum.name: cdx6500frdtepStatsPortNum
cdx6500frdtepStatsPortNum.description: Specifies a specific port in the network diagram.

cdx6500frdtepPortStatus.name: cdx6500frdtepPortStatus
cdx6500frdtepPortStatus.description: Specifies the current port status. disabled - Port has been disabled. enabled - Port is operational. busyOut - Port has been busied out. up - Port is operational. down - Port is down. na - Value not Available.

cdx6500frdtepUtilizationIn.name: cdx6500frdtepUtilizationIn
cdx6500frdtepUtilizationIn.description: Factor determined by comparison of volume (characters per second) of data and clock rate for a specific port.

cdx6500frdtepUtilizationOut.name: cdx6500frdtepUtilizationOut
cdx6500frdtepUtilizationOut.description: Factor determined by comparison of volume (characters per second) of data and clock rate for a specific port.

cdx6500frdtepCharInTotal.name: cdx6500frdtepCharInTotal
cdx6500frdtepCharInTotal.description: Number of characters received since last boot or statistics reset.

cdx6500frdtepCharOutTotal.name: cdx6500frdtepCharOutTotal
cdx6500frdtepCharOutTotal.description: Number of characters transmitted since last boot or statistics reset.

cdx6500frdtepCharsInPerSec.name: cdx6500frdtepCharsInPerSec
cdx6500frdtepCharsInPerSec.description: Average number of characters received per second.

cdx6500frdtepCharsOutPerSec.name: cdx6500frdtepCharsOutPerSec
cdx6500frdtepCharsOutPerSec.description: Average number of characters transmitted per second.

cdx6500frdtepFrameInTotal.name: cdx6500frdtepFrameInTotal
cdx6500frdtepFrameInTotal.description: Number of frames received since last boot or statistics reset.

cdx6500frdtepFrameOutTotal.name: cdx6500frdtepFrameOutTotal
cdx6500frdtepFrameOutTotal.description: Number of frames transmitted since last boot or statistics reset.

cdx6500frdtepFramesInPerSec.name: cdx6500frdtepFramesInPerSec
cdx6500frdtepFramesInPerSec.description: Average number of frames received per second.

cdx6500frdtepFramesOutPerSec.name: cdx6500frdtepFramesOutPerSec
cdx6500frdtepFramesOutPerSec.description: Average number of frames transmitted per second.

cdx6500frdtepOverrunErrors.name: cdx6500frdtepOverrunErrors
cdx6500frdtepOverrunErrors.description: An input buffer overflowed and characters were discarded.

cdx6500frdtepUnderrunErrors.name: cdx6500frdtepUnderrunErrors
cdx6500frdtepUnderrunErrors.description: Number of errors detected since last node boot or reset of statistics.

cdx6500frdtepCRCErrors.name: cdx6500frdtepCRCErrors
cdx6500frdtepCRCErrors.description: Number of errors detected by Cyclic Redundancy Check since last node boot reset of statistics.

cdx6500SPCTFRDTEStationTable.name: cdx6500SPCTFRDTEStationTable
cdx6500SPCTFRDTEStationTable.description: All of the configuration parameters relevant to the Frame Relay DTE Station table.

cdx6500SPCTFRDTEStationEntry.name: cdx6500SPCTFRDTEStationEntry
cdx6500SPCTFRDTEStationEntry.description: A row of Frame Realy DTE station configuration parameters.

cdx6500frdtesCfgDLCI.name: cdx6500frdtesCfgDLCI
cdx6500frdtesCfgDLCI.description: The Data Link Connection Identifier (dlci) is the unique identifier for the station on the FRI Port. Its valid range is 16 - 1007. It must match the DLCI configured on the FR Networking Node.

cdx6500frdtesStationType.name: cdx6500frdtesStationType
cdx6500frdtesStationType.description: Identifies the type of station being configured. annexG - This station uses X.25 signaling for layer 3 bypass - This station type bypasses layer 3. There is no signaling for SVC's on this station. voiceRelay - Not used in the current version.

cdx6500frdtesCommInfoRate.name: cdx6500frdtesCommInfoRate
cdx6500frdtesCommInfoRate.description: This parameter (CIR) specifies the rate (in bits-per-second) that the Frame Relay network agrees to transfer information under congested conditions for the FRI Station. This value is used to throttle data on the FRI station for congestion control purposes. The CIR cannot be greater than the link speed.

cdx6500frdtesCommBurstSize.name: cdx6500frdtesCommBurstSize
cdx6500frdtesCommBurstSize.description: This parameter (BC) specifies the maximum amount of data (in bits) that the Frame Relay network agrees to transfer over a time interval T = Committed Burst Size / Committed Information Rate. Must be > 1/20th of the Committed Information Rate. This is used for congestion control purposes.

cdx6500frdtesTransDelay.name: cdx6500frdtesTransDelay
cdx6500frdtesTransDelay.description: This parameter is the expected one-way delay through the network. This is specified in milliseconds.

cdx6500frdtesControlledMode.name: cdx6500frdtesControlledMode
cdx6500frdtesControlledMode.description: This parameter controls the method of congestion control: normal - congestion control is normal disable - never enter Congested State (CTRL) congested - never enter a Non-Congested State (UCTRL) limit - congestion control is normal but limits the data rate to no lower than CIR. nc - Skipped during configuration

cdx6500frdtesLinkAddress.name: cdx6500frdtesLinkAddress
cdx6500frdtesLinkAddress.description: The logical link address must be set to complementary values in this FRI station and its corresponding remote FRI station: dte - station to have logical DTE address (A) dce - station to have logical DCE address (B) nc - Skipped during configuration.

cdx6500frdtesPVCChannels.name: cdx6500frdtesPVCChannels
cdx6500frdtesPVCChannels.description: Number of logical channels used for Permanent Virtual Circuits. The total number of PVC and SVC channels on a station (logical link) should be kept as small as possible and consistent with needs. PVC connections must be configured in the PVC Table.

cdx6500frdtesStartingPVC.name: cdx6500frdtesStartingPVC
cdx6500frdtesStartingPVC.description: This is the starting logical channel number for the Permanent Virtual Circuits on this FRI station. Not used if the number of PVCs = 0.

cdx6500frdtesSVCChannels.name: cdx6500frdtesSVCChannels
cdx6500frdtesSVCChannels.description: Number of logical channels used in Switched Virtual Circuits. The total number of PVC and SVC channels on a station (logical link) should be kept as small as possible and consistent with needs.

cdx6500frdtesStartingSVC.name: cdx6500frdtesStartingSVC
cdx6500frdtesStartingSVC.description: This is the starting logical channel number for the Switched Virtual Circuits on this station (logical link). Not used if the number of SVCs = 0.

cdx6500frdtesInitialFrame.name: cdx6500frdtesInitialFrame
cdx6500frdtesInitialFrame.description: Specify the initial frame required by other end for (logical) link startup: none - do nothing (other end initiates link-up) sabm - send SABM disc - send DISC, then SABM nc - Skipped during configuration

cdx6500frdtesRetryTimer.name: cdx6500frdtesRetryTimer
cdx6500frdtesRetryTimer.description: T1 link retry timer value in tenths of a second (e.g. 30 = 3.0 seconds).

cdx6500frdtesPollTimer.name: cdx6500frdtesPollTimer
cdx6500frdtesPollTimer.description: This sets the time an idle link is probed for assurance of connection to the remote FRI station. 0 - disable the timer X - X is in tenths of a second (e.g. 40 = 4.0 seconds) and must be set greater than T1.

cdx6500frdtesTries.name: cdx6500frdtesTries
cdx6500frdtesTries.description: The maximum number of attempts allowed to complete a transmission.

cdx6500frdtesFrameWinSize.name: cdx6500frdtesFrameWinSize
cdx6500frdtesFrameWinSize.description: Frame level window size must be set to the same value at both this FRI station and the remote FRI station.

cdx6500frdtesPacketWinSize.name: cdx6500frdtesPacketWinSize
cdx6500frdtesPacketWinSize.description: Packet level window size must be set to the same value at both this FRI station and the remote FRI station.

cdx6500frdtesMaxPacketSize.name: cdx6500frdtesMaxPacketSize
cdx6500frdtesMaxPacketSize.description: This is the maximum X.25 packet size used on the station (logical link). For proper operation, this must be set to the same value at both this FRI station and the remote FRI station. nc - Skipped during configuration.

cdx6500frdtesUpperQueue.name: cdx6500frdtesUpperQueue
cdx6500frdtesUpperQueue.description: This is the maximum number of data packets a channel on this station (logical link) will queue for transmission before invoking flow control to the attached channel

cdx6500frdtesLowerQueue.name: cdx6500frdtesLowerQueue
cdx6500frdtesLowerQueue.description: This is the number of data packets a channel on this FRI station will have queued for transmission when it releases flow control to the attached channel

cdx6500frdtesRestartTimer.name: cdx6500frdtesRestartTimer
cdx6500frdtesRestartTimer.description: Restart-Request timeout timer in seconds. If timer expires on this FRI station, the Restart request is sent again.

cdx6500frdtesResetTimer.name: cdx6500frdtesResetTimer
cdx6500frdtesResetTimer.description: Reset-Request timeout timer in seconds. If timer expires on this FRI station, the Reset request is sent again.

cdx6500frdtesCallTimer.name: cdx6500frdtesCallTimer
cdx6500frdtesCallTimer.description: Call-Request timeout timer in seconds. If timer expires on this FRI station, the call is cleared.

cdx6500frdtesClearTimer.name: cdx6500frdtesClearTimer
cdx6500frdtesClearTimer.description: Clear-Request timeout timer in seconds. If timer expires on this FRI station, the Clear request is sent again.

cdx6500frdtesX25Options.name: cdx6500frdtesX25Options
cdx6500frdtesX25Options.description: Select X.25 options on this station (logical link) as follows: NONE - no option specified CUG - check closed user group; otherwise, CUG passes transparently CAUSE - pass cause, diagnostic, code in outbound packets HOLD - hold calls over link restart INL - inter-node link. Link goes to another 6500 device DELAY - Enable Delay and Path Trace on this link (link must be connected to Rel. 4.xx node) Any combination of above specified by summing (e.g. CUG+CAUSE+. . .). NOTE: Please use cdx6500frdtesStnX25Options, which has been added to replace this object.

cdx6500frdtesRCDestination.name: cdx6500frdtesRCDestination
cdx6500frdtesRCDestination.description: All calls entering this station will be routed to the destination specified in this parameter, irrespective of route selection table entries. For example, to route all calls to X.25 port 3, use X25-3. To route calls to FRI port 2, station 4, use FRI-2S4. Blank this field to disable this function.

cdx6500frdtesCUG.name: cdx6500frdtesCUG
cdx6500frdtesCUG.description: The station may be a member of up to 8 different Closed User Groups (CUGs). Each CUG membership must be a two digit number and separated by a comma. (e.g. 12,34,56,09,02,03 ). Two hyphens following each oher indicates no CUG Membership 00-99 - CUG Membership

cdx6500frdtesBillingRecords.name: cdx6500frdtesBillingRecords
cdx6500frdtesBillingRecords.description: This controls whether billing (accounting) records will be created for calls on this FRI station. off - Billing records will not be created. on - Billing records will be created. nc - Skipped during configuration.

cdx6500frdtesCfgStationNum.name: cdx6500frdtesCfgStationNum
cdx6500frdtesCfgStationNum.description: The number of the logical link on the line. This is the value of Sxx for routing purposes.

cdx6500frdtesStnX25Options.name: cdx6500frdtesStnX25Options
cdx6500frdtesStnX25Options.description: Select X.25 options on this station (logical link) as follows: NONE - no option specified CUG - check closed user group; otherwise, CUG passes transparently CAUSE - pass cause, diagnostic, code in outbound packets HOLD - hold calls over link restart INL - inter-node link. Link goes to another 6500 device DELAY - Enable Delay and Path Trace on this link (link must be connected to Rel. 4.xx node) Any combination of above specified by summing (e.g. CUG+CAUSE+. . .). NOTE: This object has been added to replace cdx6500frdtesX25Options.

cdx6500frdtesStnFrameSegmenter.name: cdx6500frdtesStnFrameSegmenter
cdx6500frdtesStnFrameSegmenter.description: Determine if this station will support the Frame Segmenter Header.The Frame Segmenter should be enabled if the frame relay port is configured to pass voice traffic. disabled - Frame Segmenter disabled. enabled - Frame Segmenter enabled. nc - Skipped during configuration.

cdx6500frdtesStnVoiceSVCChannels.name: cdx6500frdtesStnVoiceSVCChannels
cdx6500frdtesStnVoiceSVCChannels.description: Number of logical voice channels used in Switched Virtual Circuits.The total number of voice and data channels on a station (logical link) should be kept as small as possible and consistent with needs.

cdx6500frdtesStnVoiceCongCtrlMode.name: cdx6500frdtesStnVoiceCongCtrlMode
cdx6500frdtesStnVoiceCongCtrlMode.description: This parameter controls the method of voice congestion control: enabled - Station is forced into congestion when voice calls are detected. disabled - Station operates normally Use this parameter in voice applications, when the frame relay network can have more than 140ms of data buffered. One typical application is asymmetrical speeds. When this parameter is enabled, and voice is detected, delta T is forced to 50 ms and the BC is forced to 1/20 CIR.

cdx6500frdtesStnPeakUtilization.name: cdx6500frdtesStnPeakUtilization
cdx6500frdtesStnPeakUtilization.description: The monitoring interval size specifies the time period to use when monitoring peak data link/CIR (Committed Information Rate) utilization. 0 - Disables this monitoring feature. 1 to 240 - The number of 64 second increments to use for the monitoring interval time period. For example: a value of 30 specifies a time duration equal to 30 * 64 seconds = 1920 seconds or 32 minutes.

cdx6500frdtesStnMaxInboundQueue.name: cdx6500frdtesStnMaxInboundQueue
cdx6500frdtesStnMaxInboundQueue.description: This specifies the maximum number of frames from the network which may be queued in a BYPASS station. A smaller value may ve choosen for applications which experience objectable delays, if due to excessive growth of the BYPASS inbound queue.

cdx6500frdtesStnAnnexGRateReduction.name: cdx6500frdtesStnAnnexGRateReduction
cdx6500frdtesStnAnnexGRateReduction.description: This parameter determines whether Annex G stations will invoke implicit congestion control when a link error is detected, reducing their transmitted information rate to 1/4 CIR. The rate will be gradually increased in the normal way as non-BECN frames are received.

cdx6500SPSTFRDTEStationTable.name: cdx6500SPSTFRDTEStationTable
cdx6500SPSTFRDTEStationTable.description: All of the statistics parameters relevant to the Frame Relay DTE Station (DLCI) table.

cdx6500SPSTFRDTEStationEntry.name: cdx6500SPSTFRDTEStationEntry
cdx6500SPSTFRDTEStationEntry.description: A row of Frame Relay DTE station (DLCI) Statistics parameters.

cdx6500frdtesStatsPortNum.name: cdx6500frdtesStatsPortNum
cdx6500frdtesStatsPortNum.description: Specifies a specific port in the network diagram.

cdx6500frdtesStatsDLCI.name: cdx6500frdtesStatsDLCI
cdx6500frdtesStatsDLCI.description: Data Link Connection Identifier is the unique identifier for the station on the FRI port and must match the DLCI configured on the Frame Relay networking node.

cdx6500frdtesUtilizationIn.name: cdx6500frdtesUtilizationIn
cdx6500frdtesUtilizationIn.description: Indicates the quantity of user bytes sent down the link expressed as a percentage of the maximum number of bytes that could have been sent.

cdx6500frdtesUtilizationOut.name: cdx6500frdtesUtilizationOut
cdx6500frdtesUtilizationOut.description: Indicates the quantity of user bytes sent down the link expressed as a percentage of the maximum number of bytes that could have been sent.

cdx6500frdtesMaxSVCCount.name: cdx6500frdtesMaxSVCCount
cdx6500frdtesMaxSVCCount.description: Maximum number of SVCs available in the network.

cdx6500frdtesCurrentSVCCount.name: cdx6500frdtesCurrentSVCCount
cdx6500frdtesCurrentSVCCount.description: Current number of SVCs currently in use.

cdx6500frdtesCharInTotal.name: cdx6500frdtesCharInTotal
cdx6500frdtesCharInTotal.description: Number of characters received since last node boot or statistics reset.

cdx6500frdtesCharOutTotal.name: cdx6500frdtesCharOutTotal
cdx6500frdtesCharOutTotal.description: Number of characters transmitted since last node boot or statistics reset.

cdx6500frdtesCharsInPerSec.name: cdx6500frdtesCharsInPerSec
cdx6500frdtesCharsInPerSec.description: Average number of characters received per second.

cdx6500frdtesCharsOutPerSec.name: cdx6500frdtesCharsOutPerSec
cdx6500frdtesCharsOutPerSec.description: Average number of characters transmitted per second.

cdx6500frdtesPktInTotal.name: cdx6500frdtesPktInTotal
cdx6500frdtesPktInTotal.description: Number of packets received since last node boot or statistics reset.

cdx6500frdtesPktOutTotal.name: cdx6500frdtesPktOutTotal
cdx6500frdtesPktOutTotal.description: Number of packets transmitted since last node boot or statistics reset.

cdx6500frdtesPktsInPerSec.name: cdx6500frdtesPktsInPerSec
cdx6500frdtesPktsInPerSec.description: Average number of packets received per second.

cdx6500frdtesPktsOutPerSec.name: cdx6500frdtesPktsOutPerSec
cdx6500frdtesPktsOutPerSec.description: Average number of packets transmitted per second.

cdx6500frdtesPacketsQueued.name: cdx6500frdtesPacketsQueued
cdx6500frdtesPacketsQueued.description: Current number of packets buffered since last node boot or statistics reset.

cdx6500frdtesFrameInTotal.name: cdx6500frdtesFrameInTotal
cdx6500frdtesFrameInTotal.description: Number of frames received since last node boot or statistics reset.

cdx6500frdtesFrameOutTotal.name: cdx6500frdtesFrameOutTotal
cdx6500frdtesFrameOutTotal.description: Number of frames transmitted since last node boot or statistics reset.

cdx6500frdtesFramesInPerSec.name: cdx6500frdtesFramesInPerSec
cdx6500frdtesFramesInPerSec.description: Average number of frames received per second.

cdx6500frdtesFramesOutPerSec.name: cdx6500frdtesFramesOutPerSec
cdx6500frdtesFramesOutPerSec.description: Average number of frames transmitted per second.
